verbs.description: [ARG0: Groups] [V: opposed] [ARG1: to California 's new sanctuary state law] plan to show up Tuesday morning at the Placer County Board of Supervisors meeting as they want to join a growing list of counties protesting the law protecting illegal immigrants . However , the topic is not even on the morning agenda and the board chairman has been quoted as saying there is " no purpose " to even discuss the issue since it 's already been litigated and will be resolved in the courts . Even still , Republican groups sent out an advisory saying they will be in attendance to push the issue and ask to it to be included on the agenda for a public hearing later this month . Several California cities and counties have weighed in on the issue of SB 54 , which critics say violates federal law enforcement rights to information about undocumented immigrants in jail . -- MORE ON KCRA + + Another California county backs Trump 's ' sanctuary ' lawsuit + + California city wants exemption from sanctuary state law + + More local CA governments opposing sanctuary policies + + California county votes to join Trump 's ' sanctuary ' lawsuit

Even still , Republican groups sent out an advisory saying they will be in attendance to push the issue and ask to it to be included on the agenda for a public hearing later this month .
